<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880422-0193 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Robert D. Richley Is Named President Of First City Bancorp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WNEWS FBT </CO><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Robert D. Richley was named president and chief operating officer of First City Bancorp. of Texas, the bank holding company rescued in a $1.5 billion federally assisted bailout earlier this week.    Mr. Richley, 44 years old, previously was president and chief executive officer of First National Corp., San Diego. In the late 1970s and early 1980s, he worked with First City's chairman and chief executive officer, A. Robert Abboud, at First Chicago Corp. and Occidental Petroleum Corp. He also has been an executive of Crocker National Bank and of Krupp Co.    At First City, Mr. Richley will oversee the company's commercial and consumer banking activities as it tries to win back depositors and customer confidence following the bailout.    Prior to this week's bailout, Daniel C. Arnold, 57, was First City's chairman, president and chief executive. The company didn't have a chief operating officer. </TEXT></DOC>